'''Melvin Feyçal Mastil''' (born 19 February 2000) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for the [[Challenge League (Switzerland)|Swiss Challenge League]] club [[FC Stade Nyonnais|Stade Nyonnais]], on loan from [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne-Sport]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

==Club career==
A youth product of the Swiss club [[FC Echichens|Echichens]], Mastil transferred to [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne-Sport]]'s reserve side [[FC Lausanne-Sport|FC Azzurri 90 LS]] on 16 August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://journaldemorges.ch/sports/melvin-mastil-veut-prendre-son-envol/https%3A%2F%2Fjournaldemorges.ch%2Fsports%2Fmelvin-mastil-veut-prendre-son-envol|title=Melvin Mastil veut prendre son envol|website=Melvin Mastil veut prendre son envol}}</ref> The following season he moved to [[FC Echallens|Echallens]], before moving to Lausanne-Sport on loan on 18 February 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lacote.ch/sport/football/du-fc-echichens-au-ls-en-deux-ans-la-folle-trajectoire-de-melvin-mastil-1046772|title=Du FC Echichens au LS en deux ans: la folle trajectoire de Melvin Mastil|website=Du FC Echichens au LS en deux ans: la folle trajectoire de Melvin Mastil}}</ref> He permanently transferred to Lausanne-Sport on 27 July 2021 on a 3-year contract, and was named their third goalkeeper.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lausanne-sport.ch/trois-lausannois-signent-leur-premier-contrat-pro/|title=TROIS LAUSANNOIS SIGNENT LEUR PREMIER CONTRAT PRO!|first=Vincent|last=Steinmann|date=27 July 2021}}</ref> On 8 March 2023, he extended his contract with Lausanne-Sport until 2027.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lausanne-sport.ch/melvin-mastil-dans-la-duree-avec-le-ls/|title=MELVIN MASTIL DANS LA DURÉE AVEC LE LS!|first=Vincent|last=Steinmann|date=8 March 2023}}</ref> On 27 June 2023, he joined [[FC Biel-Bienne|Biel-Bienne]] on a year-long loan in the [[Swiss Promotion League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lausanne-sport.ch/melvin-mastil-au-fc-bienne-pour-la-saison/|title=MELVIN MASTIL EN PRÊT AU FC BIENNE POUR LA SAISON|first=Vincent|last=Steinmann|date=27 June 2023}}</ref> On 18 June 2024, he joined [[FC Stade Nyonnais|Stade Nyonnais]] on loan in the [[Swiss Challenge League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lausanne-sport.ch/melvin-mastil-en-pret-a-stade-nyonnais/|title=Melvin Mastil en prêt à Stade Nyonnais|first=Vincent|last=Steinmann|date=18 June 2024}}</ref> On 7 January 2026, he extended his contract with his parent club Lausanne-Sport until 2029.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lausanne-sport.ch/melvin-mastil-lausannois-jusquen-2029/|title=Melvin Mastil lausannois jusqu’en 2029|date=7 January 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Mastil moved to Switzerland at the age of 6, and is of Algerian descent through a grandfather.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Maghreb-fc-le-blog-de-nabil-djellit-melvin-mastil-le-gardien-qui-reve-des-fennecs-ce-serait-une-enorme-fierte-de-representer-l-algerie/1655513|title=Maghreb FC, le blog de Nabil Djellit - Melvin Mastil, le gardien qui rêve des Fennecs : " Ce serait une énorme fierté de représenter l'Algérie "|website=L'Équipe}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]] for a set of friendlies in March 2026.<ref>{{cite web|title=Algeria: Petkovic's squad announced with 6 new faces!|url=https://foot-africa.com/en/news/algeria-petkovics-squad-announced-with-6-new-faces-1130582/|website=Foot-Africa.com|date=18 March 2026|access-date=22 March 2026}}</ref> He debuted with Algeria in a 7–0 friendly win over [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]] on 27 March 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.el-balad.com/16894198|title=Algérie – Guatemala en direct: Zidane écarté, Mastil titulaire à Gênes - El-Balad.com}}</ref>

